Description: Casio MIDI Guitar MG510 in factory hard case No apparent modifications and comes with the original manual The guitar itself has an awesome action and sounds great. Very Strat like. The MIDI controls all work perfectly. This rare guitar is super fun to play especially if you hook a MIDI cable and guitar cable at the same time. Eg: Driving guitar and sweeping strings at the same time. Very cool :-) You can run the MIDI off 6 x 1.5 volt AA batteries or a 9 volt adapter (not included) I hate having to part with this guitar but I have bills to pay. Thanks and happy bidding!
Title: Casio Midi Guitar MG510 in original hard case!
Subtitle: Works perfectly!
ConditionDescription: The guitar has one or two dings on the body and a small chip on the top of the headstock. It also has some slight scratches on the back of the body from rubbing against belt buckles when played. The plastic tip for the pickup selector is missing but cheap to replace. The hard case has some slight marks and scratches but otherwise in great condition. Tested the MIDI and guitar pickups before listing and they work perfectly!
